race.comment: THUNDER SHOC (5) is a progressive mare that has been going through her grades nicely this campaign. She maps well from the good draw and is sure to be thereabouts again. UP THE DEN (3) did enough first-up and is sure to improve having won second up in the past. Lightly-raced and has good upside. He will roll forward and can take some catching. KALASEC (2) is working towards another win and must be considered an each-way chance. Will get back but in a small field won't have to spot the leaders too much of a start upon straightening. PALM OF JUMEIRAH (6) might be able to run a cheeky race first-up as she has done in the past.
